description: FluidDensityFlow is a simple and handy app designed for engineers and technicians working with valves, pipes, and flow systems. It helps you perform quick calculations related to fluid flow, pressure, temperature, and mechanical strength — all in one place. The app includes useful tools like mass flow rate, pipe velocity, and valve size suggestion to make your work faster and easier. You can also check choked flow, leakage rate, and pressure ratios with just a few inputs. For mechanical checks, it calculates safety factors and actuator power demands with simple formulas. FluidDensityFlow is built to save time, reduce manual work, and support accurate results in daily engineering tasks. It’s your easy companion for smart and reliable flow system calculations.

ViscosityOptimiserTool is a  easy-to-use app for pump and fluid engineers. It helps you quickly analyse how viscosity and cavitation affect pump performance. The tool includes simple calculators for viscosity correction, suction performance, and cavitation checks. You can easily estimate inducer size, eye diameter, and inlet blade angles for better pump design. It also helps assess tip speed effects, impeller trimming impact, and non-Newtonian flow behaviour. With clear inputs and instant results, the app saves time and improves accuracy. Whether for design, testing, or troubleshooting, ViscosityOptimiserTool makes fluid calculations simple and reliable.

SpanSurveyTrker is a field app to help teams check and record power line patrols with less hassle and fewer mistakes. Inspectors can log each patrol with date, time, GPS spot, span or tower number, weather, issues found, and how serious the problem is, all in one place. Wire height checks are easy too, with simple forms for span ID, GPS, measured height, tool used, and field notes. The app keeps all patrol and wire height records tidy and ready to review later. Built-in converters let you switch load and force units (N, kN, kgf, lbf) and angle units (degrees, radians, slope %) in a few taps. You can also change GPS coordinates between DMS and decimal degrees without leaving the app. Extra tools convert speed (m/s, km/h, mph), tension (kN, lbs, daN), and elevation or height (m, ft), so field staff do not need a calculator. SpanSurveyTrker keeps line survey work simple, clear, and fast for people working outdoors.

A game recording and analysis application specially designed for rugby fans. Help you systematically record the detailed information of each game, including opponents, scores, game results, locations, weather and other data, and understand the performance trend of the team through data analysis. Core functions: Competition record management: record opponents, scores, results, dates, places, etc. Statistical analysis of data: winning percentage, winning streak record, average score, etc. Intelligent search filtering: Quickly search by opponent, location, date and result. Performance trend analysis: monthly performance, opponent analysis, weather impact, etc. Best performance record: automatically identify the best competition and the best month.

LineSagAnalyst is a handy tool to quickly study sag and tension in overhead lines. It lets you find basic catenary sag from span, tension, and weight, and also gives sag at any point along the span. You can work backwards too, finding the tension you need to get a target sag. A temperature tool helps you see how sag changes on hot or cold days. Extra load tools let you check sag with ice on the conductor and find the horizontal tension when wind is blowing. You can also check line clearance along a ground profile to be sure safety gaps are met. Field helpers let you estimate span length from a simple angle and height reading and adjust support height to fix clearance issues. For more insight, it also compares parabolic and true catenary results and shows the percent difference.

Ski record assistant is a professional skiing data management application, which helps to record and analyze the detailed data of each skiing. Core function Detailed record: record date, place, duration, distance, maximum speed, average speed, weather, temperature and comments. Data statistics: automatically calculate the total number of records, total distance, total duration, average speed and maximum speed, etc. Visual analysis: provide trend charts of distance, speed and duration, and visually show movement changes. Intelligent analysis: location statistics, weather statistics, trend analysis, to understand sports habits. Convenient management: support search, filtering and sorting, and quickly find history.
